tasks.description:
Rewrite `useTimelineData.ts` as thin orchestrator (target: <150 LOC).

The file should contain:
1. **Imports** of all 6 sub-hooks + `useQueryClient`, `useRef`, `useVideoEditorRuntime`
2. **`UseTimelineDataResult` interface** — unchanged (lines 62-111), this is the public contract
3. **Re-exports**: `export type { SaveStatus } from './useTimelineSave'`, `export type { RenderStatus } from './useRenderState'`, `export type { ClipTab, EditorPreferences } from './useEditorPreferences'`, `export { shouldAcceptPolledData } from './useTimelineSave'`
4. **Hook body** composing in this order:
   ```
   const queryClient = useQueryClient();
   const { provider, timelineId, userId } = useVideoEditorRuntime();
   const prefs = useEditorPreferences(timelineId);
   const queries = useTimelineQueries(provider, timelineId);
   const onSaveSuccessRef = useRef<(() => void) | null>(null);
   const save = useTimelineSave(queries, provider, onSaveSuccessRef);
   const derived = useDerivedTimeline(save.data, save.selectedClipId, save.selectedTrackId);
   const render = useRenderState(derived.resolvedConfig, derived.renderMetadata);
   const assets = useAssetOperations(provider, timelineId, userId, queryClient);
   onSaveSuccessRef.current = () => render.setRenderDirty(true);
   ```
5. **Return object** merging all sub-hook results into `UseTimelineDataResult`

Verify:
- `npx tsc --noEmit` passes
- All downstream imports resolve: `useTimelineState.ts:8` (useTimelineData), `useTimelineState.ts:20` (SaveStatus, RenderStatus, EditorPreferences), `useTimelineState.types.ts:4` (typeof useTimelineData / ReturnType), `ClipPanel.tsx:12` (ClipTab), `useExternalDrop.ts:7` (UseTimelineDataResult), plus 4 other hooks importing UseTimelineDataResult
- File is under 150 LOC
